        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "Hello, \n\nI found a problem when using Zend_Controller_Router_Route_Hostname.\n\nCode below works as expected on ZF 1.7.7:\n\n{code}\n        $hostnameRoute = new Zend_Controller_Router_Route_Hostname(\n            ':locale.' . $this->_config->webhost ,\n            array(\n                'module'\t=> 'default',\n                'controller' => 'index'\n            )\n        );\n        \n        $pathRoute = new Zend_Controller_Router_Route(\n            ':controller\/:action\/*',\n            array(\n            \t'module' => 'default',\n                'controller' => 'index',\n                'action' => 'index'\n            )\n        );  \n{code}\n\npointing browser to url: http:\/\/pl.mydomain.s\/index\/splashed\/param1\/value1\/param2\/value\/param3\/value3\nreceived params:\n{code}\nArray ( [controller] => index [action] => splashed [param1] => value1 [param2] => value [param3] => value3 [module] => default [locale] => pl )\n{code}\nEverything works ok.\n\nAfter switching to ZF 1.8.1 (tested on 1.8.2 - same result):\n{code}\nArray ( [controller] => index [action] => splashed [param1] => value1 [param2] => value [param3] => value3 [module] => default)\n{code}\n\nThe 'locale' parameter is missing.\n"
        },
