                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Holger, join the club.\r\n\r\nIf you look in the issue tracker, we have over 1000 open issues (of which around 50% are bug reports). We simply do not have the resources internally at Zend or in the community to close them all out in a timely fashion.\r\n\r\nIssues with more votes and issues with attached patches (particularly those with unit tests) get precedence. Additionally, we have bug hunt days each month, and you can grab a developer during that time to see if they can look at your issue. If you want to see the issue expedited, those are your paths. ",
